{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":176,"record_hash":"sha256:a4aea5b705f37d3ba9dd186deb34a8e4c820e8ace197aa4bbad25e8ecaefe8bb","timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:12:40.391Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: d63b21\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 980\nOutput:\nFor a PR/review-id query, lookup can start from turns where a branch carried\nthat review identifier, then optionally expand through the PR branch, head\ncommits, change ids, and touched paths.\n\nFor suggestion ranking:\n\n1. scan recent sessions or turns\n2. count observed branches/stacks/review units\n3. compare previous-turn worktree files with current-turn committed files\n4. rank candidate sessions, turns, changes, branches, and PRs\n5. let UI or API confirmation decide what gets written as a relationship\n\n## Gaps To Resolve\n\n- Turn write atomicity: can transcript records, record hashes, turn objects,\n  turn-list entries, and indexes be written as one logical GitMeta update, or do\n  we need a repair path for unassigned transcript records?\n- Provider grouping: should transcript records gain an optional normalized\n  provider turn key for UI grouping, and should it be hashed/redacted?\n- Previous turn links: should each turn store a direct previous-turn pointer, or\n  should ordering be derived from timestamps and source record indexes?\n- Environment publication boundary: repo-scoped GitMeta exchange can include\n  branch names, relative file paths, PR identifiers, change ids, commit ids, and\n  commit file lists; what extra controls are needed before exposing a selected\n  web view outside normal repository access?\n- Snapshot size cap: what exact cap should path lists use before setting\n  `*_truncated = true`?\n- Index rebuild/versioning: branch, review, and change indexes are the likely\n  first set; where should rebuild behavior live, and how should stale derived\n  lookup entries be invalidated?\n- Stack model: what exact GitButler API gives the needed stack/branch/change/review\n  view in both GitButler mode and plain Git mode?\n- Checked-out references: is this a real field, or just a derived projection of\n  stacks and branches?\n- Association strength: which signals are strong enough to preselect a\n  suggested relationship?\n- Confirmation UX: should commit UI, PR/review publishing, or both ask the user\n  to confirm suggested sessions or turns?\n- Relationship scope: what is the smallest metadata shape that supports a\n  target-to-session relationship plus optional turn scope?\n- Propagation: if turn evidence points at a change id, should branch and PR\n  views derive that relationship, or should confirmed metadata be copied upward?\n- Plain Git operations: how should commits, rebases, and squashes outside\n  GitButler affect turn-derived evidence?\n\n## Implementation Implications\n\nThe current implementation in `crates/but-agentlog` already has the pieces that\nmake a turn layer plausible:\n\n- `record_transcript` snapshots a transcript file\n- `TranscriptBatch::parse` returns parsed records plus session/source metadata\n- `write_transcript_batch` filters records through `:record-hashes`\n- transcript records already carry `source_key`, `record_index`, and\n  `record_hash`\n\nThe missing piece is that `write_transcript_batch` throws away the batch\nboundary after appending records. A turn writer would need to receive the set of\nnewly accepted records and write a corresponding turn object.\n\nOne possible storage shape:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turns = list<TurnSummary JSON>\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:turn:<turn-key> = TurnDetail JSON\n```\n\nWhere `TurnSummary` is cheap to scan and `TurnDetail` contains record\nmembership plus the environment snapshot. The exact GitMeta representation needs\nchecking against list/set/record ergonomics.\n\n## Simplification Opportunity\n\nThis may also simplify deduplication conceptually:\n\n- record hashes answer \"have we stored this transcript record before?\"\n- turn membership answers \"which records were new in this capture invocation?\"\n- association evidence reads from turns instead of trying to infer everything\n  from a flat session transcript\n\nThat keeps the core POC principle intact: capture project-scoped session data\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T01:12:40.391Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}